IC Insights: DRAM ASPs soared 41% through the first eight months of 2021, rising from $3.37 in January to $4.77 in August. ASPs slipped 3% to $4.62 in September, still a 37% surge compared to the beginning of 2021.

Such a strong price increase & market rebound were expected in 2020 following a very difficult year in 2019 when DRAM ASPs fell 44%.

DRAM sales for 3Q21 came to $26B, hitting their highest quarterly levels since 3Q18 when sales were an all-time high of $28.2B.

IC Insights believes  prices for mobile DRAM & graphics DRAM will be 0%-5% in 4Q21 due primarily to shortage of IC components (severe shortages of driver ICs, power management ICs, & other peripheral circuitry) which is limiting smartphone ( $AAPL ) & GPU ( $NVDA ) production. 

Demand is there but there exists a mismatch of components which has pressured DRAM pricing ( $MU ). Shortage of IC components needs to resolve ( $TXN $SWKS )

Note: Contract pricing lags spot pricing
